Very good yakiniku chain from Japan. Slightly different menu due to different available sources, but it still is the classic Gyu Kaku experience you would find throughout Japan. The basic gist is you order various plates of raw meats and vegetables that they bring to your table that are mostly thin sliced. In the center of your table is a grill and you and your dinner guests grill the various pieces right there, then pick them up of the grill, dip them is a bit of one of the three sauces they are known for, and eat immediately. And it is just fantastic. The service can be a bit slow but the key is to order several plates at a time and place your next order once those plates arrive (or soon after). The place can be a bit expensive but they do offer great lunch specials and great combination dinner arrangements for those who have never been and don't know what to choose. But you must absolutely no matter what pick a couple of the premium kalbi selections.
